                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="235371" author="pjones" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2018 17:23:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok - thanks Sarah!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="235366" author="sarah" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2018 16:24:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I cannot  reproduce the problem with 2 trials (1 with fresh format zfs; 2 with ldiskfs first, then reformat as zfs); I think there must be some misoperation in my previous test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="235158" author="sarah" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2018 15:59:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There isn&apos;t error mesg, just a message says &quot;no pool available&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will run the command Nathaniel mentioned to get more info.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="235089" author="utopiabound" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2018 13:54:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The zpool import should be independent of the Lustre version. Do you have a log (messages and journal)?&lt;br/&gt;
 If you still have a system, can you also run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;zpool events -v
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="235065" author="adilger" created="Wed, 17 Oct 2018 22:31:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nathaniel, can you work with Sarah to understand this issue better?  It might be related to some new ZFS feature we are trying to use?  In any case, we need to understand it before 2.12 goes out the door or we could have a big compatibility problem on our hands.  Hopefully the issue is not already present in the 2.11 release, but at least relatively few people are using that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="235064" author="adilger" created="Wed, 17 Oct 2018 22:29:40 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The cannot import pool failure still exists when clean upgrade from 2.10.5 to 2.11.56. Both builds use zfs-0.7.9-1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah,&lt;br/&gt;
 are there any error messages on the console when you try to import the pool? This would be a fairly serious error if we can&apos;t upgrade from 2.10.x (which is the version almost every ZFS user is using) to 2.12&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="235063" author="sarah" created="Wed, 17 Oct 2018 22:09:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just tried upgrade from 2.11.0 to master, not seeing this problem, pool can be imported after upgrade.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="235052" author="sarah" created="Wed, 17 Oct 2018 18:29:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The cannot import pool failure still exists when clean upgrade from 2.10.5 to 2.11.56.  Both builds use zfs-0.7.9-1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227407" author="standan" created="Sun, 6 May 2018 19:04:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes it was while doing rolling upgrade/downgrade. But while doing clean upgrade/downgrade I tried to import it using both pool name and &quot;-a&quot; it didn&apos;t worked either way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227363" author="adilger" created="Sat, 5 May 2018 23:33:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Was this resolved with &quot;zfs import -a&quot;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227354" author="jamesanunez" created="Fri, 4 May 2018 21:36:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10998&quot; title=&quot;Add 2.10.0 zfs and ldiskfs images for conf-sanity test_32&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10998&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10998&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is tracking creating new images for conf-sanity test 32.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227132" author="adilger" created="Wed, 2 May 2018 18:30:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please also create new test images for conf-sanity test_32.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
